title: PHQ-9 (IPC Session 2)
description: PHQ-9 form that is intended for IPC Session 2

item.text: A place to declare values that cannot be created using FHIRPath such as Coding. Retrieve the following items has answer value using variable expression, to use the declared value.
Observation ID of PHQ-9 Session 2 Score
The next nine questions are from the Patient Health Questionnaire-9. These questions measure depression.
Over the past week, how often have you been bothered by any of the following problems?
Little interest or pleasure in doing things

extension.valueString: Poco interés o placer en hacer cosas
Little interest or pleasure in doing things
Sentirse bajo, deprimido, o sin esperanza

item.text: Trouble falling or staying asleep, or sleeping too much

extension.valueString: Dificultad para dormirse o continuar durmiendo, o dormir demasiado
Trouble falling or staying asleep, or sleeping too much

item.text: Feeling tired or having little energy

extension.valueString: Sintiéndose cansado o tener poca energía
Feeling tired or having little energy

item.text: Feeling bad about yourself or that you are a failure or have let yourself or your family down

extension.valueString: Sentirse mal con si mismo o que es un fracaso o que dejó a si mismo o a su familia
Feeling bad about yourself or that you are a failure or have let yourself or your family down

item.text: Trouble concentrating on things, such as reading or watching television
Moving or speaking so slowly that other people could have noticed. Or the opposite—being so fidgety or restless that you have been moving around a lot more than usual

extension.valueString: Moviendo o hablando tan lentamente que otras personas podrían haber notado. O el opuesto, siendo tan inquieto o agitado que se mueve mucho más que lo normal
Moving or speaking so slowly that other people could have noticed. Or the opposite—being so fidgety or restless that you have been moving around a lot more than usual

item.text: Thoughts that you would be better off dead, or of hurting yourself

extension.valueString: Pensamientos de que estaría mejor muerto o de herirse
Thoughts that you would be better off dead, or of hurting yourself

item.text: If the client endorses suicidality, please follow your agency's local safety protocol.
Note: The client endorses suicidality. Please follow your agency's local safety protocol.
How difficult have these problems made it for you to do your work, take care of things at home, or get along with other people?

Tip #1
List symptoms, describe severity (what the summed up scores mean), and impact on daily activities.

Tip #2
Please see severity levels for the PHQ-9
• 0-4 = None-minimal depression
• 5-9 = Mild depression
• 10-14 = Moderate depression
• 15-19 = Moderately severe depression
• 20-27 = Severe depression
Suggested depression severity based on PHQ-9 score
